markets.title: Will anyone involved in the Houthi groupchat leave their office before May 2025?
markets.rules_primary: If any of the persons involved in the Houthi group chat leave their office before May 1, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The persons involved are: Mike Waltz (National Security Advisor), Scott Bessent (Treasury Secretary), Brian McCormack (Chief of Staff for the National Security Council), Pete Hegseth (Secretary of Defense) , Dan Katz (Chief of Staff for the Secretary of the Treasury), Steve Witkoff (Trump Administration's special envoy to the Middle East), J.D. Vance (Vice President), Tulsi Gabbard (DNI), Susie Wiles (WH Chief of Staff), John Ratcliffe (Director of the CIA), Mike Needham (counselor and chief of staff to the Secretary of State), Marco Rubio (Secretary of State), Alex Wong (deputy national security advisor), Walker Barrett (NSC staff), or Stephen Miller (Advisor to the President).
markets.early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the event occurs.
